{{short description|laryngologist and neurobiologist}} [[File:Sir Felix Semon. Colour lithograph by Sir L. Ward (Spy), 190 Wellcome V0005368.jpg|thumb|Colour lithograph of Felix Semon]] '''Sir Felix Semon''' (1841{{Spaced en dash}}1921) was a German pioneer in [[neurobiology]] and a prominent [[laryngologist]] in the United Kingdom. He is responsible for Semon's law.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kuczkowski|first=Jerzy|last2=Plichta|first2=Lukasz|last3=Stankiewicz|first3=Czesław|date=January 2012|title=Sir Felix Semon (1849-1921): pioneer in neurolaryngology|journal=Journal of Voice: Official Journal of the Voice Foundation|volume=26|issue=1|pages=87–89|doi=10.1016/j.jvoice.2010.10.015|issn=1873-4588|pmid=21524563}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Group|first=British Medical Journal Publishing|date=1921-03-12|title=Sir FELIX SEMON, K.C.V.O., M.D., F.R.C.P.Lond|url=https://www.bmj.com/content/1/3141/404.5|journal=Br Med J|language=en|volume=1|issue=3141|pages=404–405|doi=10.1136/bmj.1.3141.404-d|pmc=2414729|issn=0007-1447}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=March 1909|title=A TESTIMONIAL TO SIR FELIX SEMON|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(01)37663-8/abstract|journal=The Lancet|language=English|volume=173|issue=4465|pages=931|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(01)37663-8|issn=0140-6736|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Vilensky|first=Joel A.|last2=Sinish|first2=Pandy R.|date=2004|title=Sir Felix Semon and Semon's law|journal=Clinical Anatomy|language=en|volume=17|issue=8|pages=605–606|doi=10.1002/ca.20045|pmid=15495171|issn=0897-3806}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Frank|first=Ira|date=1933-09-01|title=XLIX. The Influence of Sir Felix Semon on the Development of Laryngology|journal=Annals of Otology, Rhinology & Laryngology|language=en|volume=42|issue=3|pages=641–659|doi=10.1177/000348943304200301|issn=0003-4894}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Schbliegelow|first=E.|date=January 1921|title=Sir Felix Semon|journal=Acta Oto-Laryngologica|langua