{{Infobox person | name = Kul Man Ghising | image = | alt =Kul Man Ghising | caption = Kul Man Ghising | native_name = कुलमान घिसिङ | birth_name = Kulman Ghising | | birth_place = Bethan, Ramechhap | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = {{flagcountry|Nepal}}i | other_names = | education = [[Tribhuvan University]] | alma_mater =[[Tribhuvan University]] | occupation = [[Nepal Electricity Authority]] | years_active = 2016 - Present | known_for = Removing {{clarify span|text=electricity load shedding|date=October 2017}} in Nepal | home_town = [[Mahankal, Kathmandu|Mahankal]], [[Nepal]] | title = Managing Director at Nepal Electricity Authority | website = }}
'''Kulman Ghising''' is the present Managing Director of [[Nepal Electricity Authority]] (NEA) of [[Nepal]]. He is best known for his approaches in managing Electrical Demand and Supply, thus eliminating {{Clarify span|text=load shedding issues|date=October 2017}} in key residential cities in Nepal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-4238986/The-man-turned-lights-energy-starved-Nepal.html|title=The man who turned the lights on in energy-starved Nepal|work=Mail Online|access-date=2017-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/news/10282/|title=Cool man Ghising|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2017-01-30/duhu-welcomes-its-proud-son-kulman-ghising.html|title=Duhu welcomes its proud son, Kulman ghising|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/people/the-man-who-turned-the-lights-on-in-energy-starved-nepal-1661238|title=The Man Who Turned The Lights On In Energy-Starved Nepal|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nepalitimes.com/article/interview/interview-with-Kulman-Ghising,3409|title="Power to the people" - Interview - Nepali Times|first=No|last=Author|website=nepalitimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://habamoment.com/kulman-ghising-the-unsung-national-hero/|title=Kulman Ghising : The Unsung National Hero - HAB|first=|last=HAB|website=habamoment.com}}</ref>
== Background== Ghising has been associated with NEA for over two decades. Prior to being appointed as the managing director, he was serving as the project chief of Rahughat Hydroelectricity Project. Ghising had also served as the managing director of Chilime Hydropower Company Ltd under NEA.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|url=http://thehimalayantimes.com/business/kulman-ghising-appointed-nepal-electricity-authority-managing-director/|title=Kulman Ghising appointed NEA managing director|date=15 September 2016|publisher=}}</ref> He was also the Division Chief of Rural Electrification Distribution System Reinforcement Project at NEA. Ghising has more than 22 years of experience in power generation, transmission, and distribution, and trading business, which includes contract management and dispute settlement in hydropower companies.
==Career== * Managing Director - [[Nepal Electricity Authority]] (NEA) - Current * Project Chief - Rahughat Hydroelectricity Project * Managing Director - [[Chilime Hydropower Plant|Chilime Hydropower]] Company Limited * Division Chief - Rural Electrification Distribution System Reinforcement Project at NEA
==Alma Mater== * Executive MBA degree - ACE Institute of Management, Kathmandu, 2011 * Masters in Power System Engineering - [[Institute of Engineering]], Pulchowk, Kathmandu, 2003 * B.Sc. degree in Engineering (Electrical) - Regional Institute of Technology, Jamshedpur, India, 1994 * I.Sc. - [[Amrit Campus|Amrit Science Campus]], Lainchaur, Kathmandu * School Leaving Certificate (SLC) - Amar Adarsha Madhyamik Vidhayalaya, 1986
