{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Steve Roach | image = Steve Roach, Tucson (bright).jpg | caption = Steve Roach in [[Tucson]], [[Arizona]], 2013 | background = non_vocal_instrumentalist | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1955|02|16}} | birth_place = [[La Mesa, California]] | instrument = | genre = [[Ambient music|Ambient]], [[electronic music|electronic]],<ref name=AllMusic/> [[New age music|new age]] | occupation = Composer | years_active = | label = | associated_acts = | website = [http://steveroach.com/ steveroach.com] }} {{Distinguish|Steve Reich}} '''Steve Roach''' (born February 16, 1955)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.familytreelegends.com/records/calbirths?c=search&first=Steven&last=Roach&spelling=Exact&4_year=1955&4_month=0&4_day=0&5=&7=&SubmitSearch.x=0&SubmitSearch.y=0&SubmitSearch=Submit |title=California Births, 1905 - 1995 |publisher=Familytreelegends.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-05}}</ref> is an American composer and performer of [[ambient music|ambient]] [[electronic music]], whose recordings are also classified in the genres of [[space music|space]], [[drone music|drone]], and [[New-age music|new-age]].
His 2016 album ''Spiral Revelation'' received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for New Age Album of the Year at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://echoes.org/2017/11/28/60th-annual-grammy-award-nominees/ |title=Steve Roach’s Spiral Revelation nominated in New Age album category at 60th Grammys. |work=[[Echoes.org]]|date=November 28, 2017}}</ref>
==Overview== [[File:Steve Roach, SoundQuest Soundcheck Blue.jpg|thumb|right|Roach during a soundcheck at SoundQuest in October 2010, Tucson, Arizona.]] [[File:Steve Roach performing at SoundQuest 2010 (wide crop).jpg|thumb|right|Steve Roach performing at SoundQuest 2010.]] Originally a Motocross racer, at the age of 20 Roach taught himself to play the [[synthesizer]]<ref name="AllMusic">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/steve-roach-p2749 |title=Steve Roach &#124; Music Biography, Credits and Discography |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2014-08-05}}</ref> after being inspired by such influential synthesizer artists and groups as [[Tangerine Dream]], [[Klaus Schulze]], and [[Vangelis]]. His debut album ''Now'' appeared in 1982, followed by ''[[Structures from Silence]]'' in 1984. In 1986 he released his acclaimed ''Quiet Music'' series. In 1988, he released what has been described by critics as his masterpiece, the double-album ''[[Dreamtime Return]]''.<ref name = "AllMusic"/>
As Roach's approach to ambient music has matured, his compositions have typically<ref name="Gemma">"Stretch out and enjoy the soundscape" by Gemma Tarlach, [[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]], April 21, 2000.</ref> been [[Beat (music)|beat]]less. His rhythmic and [[trance music|trance-based]] groove and tribal-ambient releases, however, are nearly as numerous<ref name="Gemma"/> as his more atmospheric releases. Some recordings are strictly synthesizer-based, whereas others include ambient [[guitar]] experiments.
Other pieces, however, cross over with more ethnic and folk influences. Roach learned to play the [[digeridoo]] during his extended trips to [[Australia]] in the 1980s, and he became an early proponent<ref>"Instrument owner lauds soothing effects," [[The Advocate (Baton Rouge)]] June 7, 1998.</ref> of its use in ambient music. His work with Mexican musician [[Jorge Reyes (musician)|Jorge Reyes]] introduced Roach to [[Prehispanic]] musical elements, which he has also included in his music. These fusions established Roach as one of the founders<ref name="Gemma"/> of the tribal-ambient sound.
Roach is married to author and equine teacher [[Linda Kohanov]]{{r|spiderbytes}} (who provided vocals on some of his albums). They live in [[Tucson, Arizona]].{{r|echoesicons}}
